From: bluecat <lmhtq1991@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 30 May 2026 10:10:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Phase C-6 L43: GC barrier set loads/stores oops as capabilities

After the cpcache stride fix (L42), getstatic resolves correctly and the
template stores the field. The store base — the resolved java_mirror oop
— came back tag-0 because BarrierSetAssembler::load_at/store_at used
integer ldr/str for uncompressed T_OBJECT/T_ARRAY. An oop is a 16-byte
capability in purecap, so this stripped the tag on every oop load/store.

Fix (high-leverage — all oop access flows through here): cap-LDR/cap-STR
for the non-compressed T_OBJECT/T_ARRAY cases in load_at and store_at.
New cap_ldr/cap_str helpers dispatch on the Address mode:
  - base_plus_offset      -> cap_ldr_imm / cap_str_imm
  - base_plus_offset_reg  -> register form, choosing scaled (lsl#4, S=1,
    for oop ARRAY elements) vs unscaled (uxtx, S=0, for byte-offset FIELD
    access) from the Address index shift. Verified vs Morello clang:
      ldr c,[c,x,lsl#4]=0xA2617800  ldr c,[c,x]=0xA2616800  (S=bit12)
      str c,[c,x,lsl#4]=0xA2217802  str c,[c,x]=0xA2216802
Added Address::index_shift() to expose the index extend shift.

The first cut hardcoded lsl#4 and bounds-faulted on a putstatic whose
index register held a BYTE offset (352), not an element index — fixed by
honouring the Address shift.

RESULT: oop field/array load+store work; execution jumps ~2300 bytes
past the entire getstatic/putstatic template family into further
bytecode templates. Next fault (L45) at 0x428c9264.

Session: 43 commits, 108 build iterations, L25-L43 resolved.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

